Buy any matches, my matches buy
A page folded in four, with one London cry in ink on p. 93, a draft for a soprano cadenza in pencil on p. 94, and various other pencil notes in pencil (usually hard to decifer).
Title from first line and caption of first work, and editorial (2nd work).
Editorial title.
Manuscript in the hand of George Frideric Handel.
A complete transcription of the cadenza is to be found in Donald Burrows and Martha J. Ronish. A catalogue of Handel's musical autographs (Oxford, 1994), p. 315.
Watermark: "LVG" below fleur de lis over Strasbourg bend; countermark: "IV" (Burrows C40)
